{'book': {'publisher': 'Vintage Uk', 'synopsis': 'This work digs deep and painfully into personal experience of depression and mental illness, while also considering the wider the historical, social, biological, pharmaceutical and medical aspects and implications of the disease. Having experienced what he is writing about firsthand, Solomon describes the experience from the inside. He has also researched every aspect of depression, the historical treatment and study of "melancholy" as far back as the Greeks and Romans (who believed that cauliflower was good for depression), and through to the side effects of the pharmaceutical cocktails of the present day; case histories of people in out of mental hospitals; faith healers; the power of suggestion; and the implications for the future of Western society.', 'language': 'en', 'image': 'https://images.isbndb.com/covers/71/32/9780099277132.jpg', 'title_long': 'The Noonday Demon', 'edition': 'New Ed', 'dimensions': 'Height: 8.50392 Inches, Length: 5.31495 Inches, Weight: 1.32056894938 Pounds, Width: 1.5748 Inches', 'dimensions_structured': {'length': {'unit': 'inches', 'value': 5.31495}, 'width': {'unit': 'inches', 'value': 1.5748}, 'weight': {'unit': 'pounds', 'value': 1.32056894938}, 'height': {'unit': 'inches', 'value': 8.50392}}, 'pages': 560, 'date_published': '2002-03-31', 'subjects': ['Biographies & Memoirs', 'Memoirs'], 'authors': ['Andrew Solomon'], 'title': 'The Noonday Demon', 'isbn13': '9780099277132', 'msrp': 18.6, 'binding': 'Paperback', 'isbn': '0099277131', 'isbn10': '0099277131'}}